    <div style="margin-top: 80px;">
        <h2>FAQs about Scenic Acres Real Estate and Neighborhood</h2>
        <ol>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Where's the nearest recreational center?</h3>
                <p>The nearest recreational centre to Scenic Acres is the Melcor YMCA at Crowfoot, reachable via Nosehill Drive. There are plenty of amenities at the YMCA, including a full-size gymnasium, childminding services, a training pool, a 25m swimming pool, and a fitness studio.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Where can I find a library?</h3>
                <p>The closest library is located near the Crowfoot Crossing shopping area. Crowfoot Library provides residents with access to free Wi-Fi, after-hours book returns, computers and printers, and spaces dedicated to studying.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Which is the best place to go shopping?</h3>
                <p>Crowfoot Crossing is just next door to Scenic Acres. Grocery shopping, fast food, fine dining, a host of boutiques, and big-box stores, you will find everything here. An array of stores makes life easy for the residents of the Scenic Acres community. Supermarket chains like Safeway, M&M Food Market, Pie Junkie and quick-service restaurants like Starbucks make shopping, eating out, and running errands convenient and quick for residents.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>How do I get around?</h3>
                <p>Scenic Acres is close to several bus lines and rail lines. The commuter routes Highway 1 and Highway 2, make accessing the nearby neighbourhood and getting out of town quick and convenient. The ease of commuting has further improved with the Stoney Trail Extension Project which connects Highway 1 (Trans-Canada Highway) to Highway 2 (Deerfoot Trail).</p>
                <p>Residents can use the Nose Hill Drive NW route to reach Arbour Lake from Scenic Acres. The closest stations to the community are the Crowfoot LRT Station and the Dalhousie LRT Station. Commuting to downtown Calgary is easy via the Crowfoot LRT Station located right in the neighbourhood.</p>
                <p>If you prefer travelling shorter distances with a greener approach, there is easy access to the Bow River path system along the banks of the Bow River. The network of pedestrian and bicycle paths spanning over 31 mi lead straight to the city centre. The path system connects several major parks and green areas in Calgary. Scenic Acre residents who enjoy cycling have access to and a great opportunity to use this fantastic eco-friendly route.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
